caller_intent: Jaycee, an 18-year-old student, seeks to reinstate her canceled auto policy with National General by making partial payments over time instead of the full $348.50 required for reinstatement.
resolution_steps: Mia explains National General requires full payment ($348.50) to reinstate the policy, not partial payments.
Jaycee proposes paying $348.50 this Friday and spreading subsequent payments over the next month.
Mia clarifies that since the policy is canceled, billing details cannot be accessed until reinstatement.
Mia advises Jaycee to call back on Friday (after receiving payment) to reinstate the policy and process payments.
Mia acknowledges inability to confirm payment plan feasibility without carrier input.
knowledge_required: National General's reinstatement policies (full payment requirement)
Handling partial payment requests for reinstatement
summary: Jaycee, a financially strained student, attempts to reinstate her canceled auto policy with National General through partial payments. The agent explains the carrier's full-payment requirement, advises reinstatement after receiving funds on Friday, and acknowledges limitations in confirming payment plans without carrier input.
